1
00:00:01,460 --> 00:00:02,712
[ mouse squeaks ]

2
00:00:02,795 --> 00:00:04,005
[ penguins wenk ]

3
00:00:06,299 --> 00:00:07,383
[ all cheering ]

4
00:00:10,845 --> 00:00:11,679
[ screeches ]

5
00:00:13,389 --> 00:00:14,557
D> Adventure Time )

6
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:15,850
» Come on, grab your friends »

7
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:18,519
» We'll go to very distant lands J

8
00:00:18,603 --> 00:00:20,938
» With Jake the dog
and Finn the human

9
00:00:21,022 --> 00:00:22,398
D The fun will never end >

10
00:00:22,481 --> 00:00:24,233
D It's Adventure Time »

11
00:00:40,708 --> 00:00:42,043
[ smacks lips ]

12
00:00:42,126 --> 00:00:45,046
[ inhales deeply, exhales ]

13
00:00:48,466 --> 00:00:50,635
[ explosion ]

14
00:00:52,803 --> 00:00:53,638
[ thud ]

15
00:00:53,721 --> 00:00:55,097
[ thud ]

16
00:01:00,186 --> 00:01:02,605
That's the comet you're
supposed to follow.

17
00:01:04,565 --> 00:01:05,775
Right. Right.

18
00:01:05,858 --> 00:01:07,860
| knew that.

19
00:01:11,197 --> 00:01:12,740
Hey, be careful, okay?

20
00:01:12,823 --> 00:01:13,824
Hold on tight.

21
00:01:13,908 --> 00:01:14,742
It's okay.

22
00:01:14,825 --> 00:01:16,452
| won't ever let you go.

23
00:01:16,535 --> 00:01:18,204
[ thinking ]
That's...true.

24
00:01:29,090 --> 00:01:30,591
Wow. Already?

25
00:01:30,675 --> 00:01:31,801
That was fast.

26
00:01:31,884 --> 00:01:33,052
Yep. We're here.

27
00:01:33,135 --> 00:01:34,679
It's time to
wake up now.

28
00:01:34,762 --> 00:01:35,805
What? Now?

29
00:01:35,888 --> 00:01:36,681
Yep.

30
00:01:36,764 --> 00:01:38,432
Like, right now?

31
00:01:38,516 --> 00:01:39,809


32
00:01:40,851 --> 00:01:42,687
[ coughs ]

33
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:44,814
Ah. Where am 1?

34
00:01:44,897 --> 00:01:45,815
What the heck?

35
00:01:45,898 --> 00:01:46,941
Is that the comet?

36
00:01:47,024 --> 00:01:49,151
And a little
farming village?

37
00:01:49,235 --> 00:01:51,153
How long have
| been walking?

38
00:01:51,237 --> 00:01:53,239
Man, two whole days --

39
00:01:53,322 --> 00:01:54,198
at least.

40
00:01:54,282 --> 00:01:55,825
Wow. | need some water.

41
00:01:55,908 --> 00:01:56,784
No, wait --

42
00:01:56,867 --> 00:01:58,494
Ah...geez.

43
00:01:59,662 --> 00:02:00,621
Hmm.

44
00:02:00,705 --> 00:02:03,082
Fields are looking
a little sparse.

45
00:02:03,165 --> 00:02:04,834
Kind of runty.

46
00:02:04,917 --> 00:02:07,003
Wonder if this village
even has any wat--

47
00:02:07,086 --> 00:02:08,838
Oh, snap!
| see some!

48
00:02:08,921 --> 00:02:10,923
[ panting ]

49
00:02:11,007 --> 00:02:11,841
Excuse me, sir.

50
00:02:11,924 --> 00:02:12,967
Could | have some water?

51
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:15,011
I've been
sleepwalking for days.

52
00:02:16,387 --> 00:02:18,222
[ laughs ]
Awesome.

53
00:02:18,306 --> 00:02:21,267
[ gargles ]

54
00:02:21,350 --> 00:02:22,310
[ laughs ]

55
00:02:22,393 --> 00:02:23,269
Heck yeah!

56
00:02:23,352 --> 00:02:24,270
Thanks, little friend!

57
00:02:24,353 --> 00:02:25,688
You just totally
saved my life.

58
00:02:25,771 --> 00:02:27,273
No pun intended.

59
00:02:28,941 --> 00:02:30,943
What's the matter?
Can't talk?

60
00:02:31,027 --> 00:02:32,737
Oh. Or are you
guys Comet Boyz?

61
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:34,071
From up in there?

62
00:02:34,155 --> 00:02:36,615
Listen, I'm no expert,
but I think y'all are

63
00:02:36,699 --> 00:02:38,617
gonna need a
lot more corn.

64
00:02:38,701 --> 00:02:40,328
And it's supposed to
stand straight-up-like.

65
00:02:40,411 --> 00:02:42,538
Or maybe Comet Boyz
only need just, like,

66
00:02:42,621 --> 00:02:43,789
a little bit of limp corn?

67
00:02:43,873 --> 00:02:45,124
No, I'm a regular guy.

68
00:02:45,207 --> 00:02:47,752
I-I'm just not supposed
to talk to strangers.

69
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:50,838
WOMAN: Lionel, what did | tell you
about talking to strangers?!

70
00:02:50,921 --> 00:02:53,591
You get your butt
inside this instant!

71
00:02:53,674 --> 00:02:55,760
[ echoing ]
Human boy!

72
00:02:55,843 --> 00:02:56,886
What the...?

73
00:02:56,969 --> 00:03:00,806
The Tree Spirit does
not permit freeloaders!

74
00:03:00,890 --> 00:03:05,895
Either help fetch the escape-pod
engine or kindly move along.

75
00:03:05,978 --> 00:03:06,812
Dad?

76
00:03:06,896 --> 00:03:07,730
Wait! Wait!

77
00:03:07,813 --> 00:03:08,814
What are you doing?

78
00:03:08,898 --> 00:03:11,400
Don't come over herel

79
00:03:12,818 --> 00:03:16,030
Mm. Mm. Mm. Mm. Mm. Mm.

80
00:03:16,113 --> 00:03:17,198
Dad?

81
00:03:17,281 --> 00:03:18,491
Ptoooooo00000000!

82
00:03:18,574 --> 00:03:19,658
- MARTIN: Finn!
- FINN: Dad?

83
00:03:19,742 --> 00:03:21,494
BOTH:
What the heck are you doing here?

84
00:03:21,577 --> 00:03:22,411
What?

85
00:03:22,495 --> 00:03:23,871
You were just
yelling at me.

86
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:26,248
No, no, that was
the Tree Spirit --

87
00:03:26,332 --> 00:03:30,211
Commander of all trees,
bringer of hard times.

88
00:03:30,294 --> 00:03:31,087
Dad.

89
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:32,880
You're not falling
for it, huh?

90
00:03:32,963 --> 00:03:34,048
Well,
it was worth a try.

91
00:03:34,131 --> 00:03:35,966
You know, those little
guys down there,

92
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:38,803
they'll do anything
for the Tree Spirit.

93
00:03:38,886 --> 00:03:41,389
| got them fetching
parts to fix my escape pod

94
00:03:41,472 --> 00:03:43,432
instead of
planting their fields.

95
00:03:43,516 --> 00:03:45,393
Isn't that sweet?

96
00:03:45,476 --> 00:03:47,103
Dad, your arm.

97
00:03:47,186 --> 00:03:48,229
Oh, this?

98
00:03:48,312 --> 00:03:49,688
[ laughs ]
Yeah.

99
00:03:49,772 --> 00:03:52,942
When my ship crashed,
| got shot out of the window.

100
00:03:53,025 --> 00:03:55,027
| knocked a kite
out of the air,

101
00:03:55,111 --> 00:03:58,823
then caught my arm
in a woodpecker hole.

102
00:03:58,906 --> 00:03:59,824
Whoa.

103
00:03:59,907 --> 00:04:01,075
But it's cool,
you know.

104
00:04:01,158 --> 00:04:02,326
Arms come and go.

105
00:04:02,410 --> 00:04:04,036
It's family
that's important.

106
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,287
[ tink! ]

107
00:04:05,371 --> 00:04:08,791
Speaking of arms, though,
| see you got yourself a

108
00:04:08,874 --> 00:04:09,792
brand-spankin'-new one.

109
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:11,293
How about that?!

110
00:04:11,377 --> 00:04:12,545
Oh. Yeah.

111
00:04:12,628 --> 00:04:14,880
| got it from my
P.B. Dream sword.

112
00:04:14,964 --> 00:04:15,840
Uh-huh. Neat.

113
00:04:15,923 --> 00:04:17,716
Actually,
for a while there,

114
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,009
| thought if |
ever saw you again,

115
00:04:19,093 --> 00:04:20,970
| was gonna tear
Yyour arm off.

116
00:04:21,053 --> 00:04:21,971
Well, shoot.

117
00:04:22,054 --> 00:04:23,472
Who could blame you?
Yeah.

118
00:04:23,556 --> 00:04:27,059
But you definitely don't feel
that way anymore, right?

119
00:04:27,143 --> 00:04:28,310
No. No.

120
00:04:28,394 --> 00:04:29,979
It's --
it's okay now.

121
00:04:30,062 --> 00:04:30,980
[ laughs ]

122
00:04:31,063 --> 00:04:32,231
Great! Great.

123
00:04:32,314 --> 00:04:33,566
How about a hug?

124
00:04:33,649 --> 00:04:35,067
[ grunts ]

125
00:04:35,151 --> 00:04:36,318
What the heck, Dad?!

126
00:04:36,402 --> 00:04:38,070
Is everything
you say a lie?

127
00:04:38,154 --> 00:04:40,030
No, no. '‘course not.

128
00:04:40,114 --> 00:04:42,992
Well [scoffs] is there any
way | can tell the difference?

129
00:04:43,075 --> 00:04:44,326
[ laughs ]

130
00:04:44,410 --> 00:04:45,202
| hope not.

131
00:04:45,286 --> 00:04:46,203
[ bell rings ]

132
00:04:46,287 --> 00:04:48,038
Hot dang!
Hold that thought.

133
00:04:48,122 --> 00:04:51,459
Those little guys are back with
the engine bulb for my pod.

134
00:04:51,542 --> 00:04:52,877
Excuse me.

135
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:56,672
[ echoing ]
I am sending forth my holy emissary,

136
00:04:56,755 --> 00:05:01,385
Martin Mertens,
and his regular son, Finn.

137
00:05:01,469 --> 00:05:05,055
Don't forget to do
whatever Martin tells you!

138
00:05:06,432 --> 00:05:07,266
Almost there.

139
00:05:07,349 --> 00:05:08,267
Little further.

140
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:09,518
Uh-huh.
Little further.

141
00:05:09,602 --> 00:05:10,519
Keep it coming.

142
00:05:10,603 --> 00:05:11,437
There you go.

143
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,856
A Jittle further.

144
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:16,984
And...stop.

145
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:18,235
Fantastic work, boys.

146
00:05:18,319 --> 00:05:19,487
Absolutely fantastic.

147
00:05:19,570 --> 00:05:20,488
[ all panting ]

148
00:05:20,571 --> 00:05:22,364
Holy stonk, dad!

149
00:05:22,448 --> 00:05:23,491
You're messing them all up!

150
00:05:23,574 --> 00:05:25,159
This is why you're
lying to them?

151
00:05:25,242 --> 00:05:26,994
So they'll mess
themselves up for you?

152
00:05:27,077 --> 00:05:28,329
Wha?! No, no, no!

153
00:05:28,412 --> 00:05:30,706
Look --
they love it. See?

154
00:05:30,789 --> 00:05:32,374
Goochy goochy goo!
[ giggles ]

155
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:33,334
Goochy goochy!

156
00:05:33,417 --> 00:05:34,210
[ giggles ]

157
00:05:34,293 --> 00:05:37,963
They're helping a poor, old,
stranded man in need.

158
00:05:38,047 --> 00:05:39,965
You like to help
people, don't you?

159
00:05:40,049 --> 00:05:41,800
I-I'd do it myself if | could,

160
00:05:41,884 --> 00:05:45,137
but I'm too strong to fit
through the service hatches.

161
00:05:46,889 --> 00:05:49,683
Come on! Gimme a chance!

162
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:50,851
[ grunts ]

163
00:05:50,935 --> 00:05:52,811
They're gonna fetch
me one last piece,

164
00:05:52,895 --> 00:05:54,980
and you and | can
watch them do it.

165
00:05:55,064 --> 00:05:57,983
Then I'll be out of your
hair by tomorrow morning.

166
00:05:58,067 --> 00:05:59,527
Oh. Right.

167
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:01,111
Yeah, don't worry.

168
00:06:01,195 --> 00:06:03,989
| know I'm cramping your style
down here, am | right, huh?

169
00:06:04,073 --> 00:06:05,533
Uh...yeah.

170
00:06:05,616 --> 00:06:06,575
Yeah, |-l guess.

171
00:06:06,659 --> 00:06:07,618
MARTIN:
Sure | am!

172
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,954
Now let's go
fetch that piece.

173
00:06:12,957 --> 00:06:15,084
It's really
warm down here.

174
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:16,085
[ gasps ]
Whoal!

175
00:06:16,168 --> 00:06:17,253
Well, yeah, son.

176
00:06:17,336 --> 00:06:19,046
That's just
the ship cooking.

177
00:06:19,129 --> 00:06:22,049
One thing about this ship --
it cooks.

178
00:06:22,132 --> 00:06:23,467
Should it be cooking?

179
00:06:23,551 --> 00:06:25,386
Nah, but that's
just real life.

180
00:06:25,469 --> 00:06:28,222
Okay, babies,
| need this piece.

181
00:06:28,305 --> 00:06:29,473
It's a steering wheel.

182
00:06:29,557 --> 00:06:31,392
It's in the steering room.

183
00:06:34,436 --> 00:06:35,688
[ sighs ]

184
00:06:35,771 --> 00:06:38,899
Last one in breaks
Tree Spirit's heart!

185
00:06:38,983 --> 00:06:40,317
Wait! Wait!
W-w-wait!

186
00:06:40,401 --> 00:06:42,570
You don't have to go in
there if you don't want to.

187
00:06:42,653 --> 00:06:45,114
Nah, | think we want to.

188
00:06:49,201 --> 00:06:50,661
Okay, | know, | know.

189
00:06:50,744 --> 00:06:54,039
Listen, that's the last
piece of the pod, right?

190
00:06:54,123 --> 00:06:58,586
Well, | promise I'll make it up
to the little boogers tonight.

191
00:06:58,669 --> 00:06:59,628
[ laughs ]

192
00:06:59,712 --> 00:07:00,629
Come here!

193
00:07:01,589 --> 00:07:03,674
[ tribal music plays ]

194
00:07:07,261 --> 00:07:09,096
Live it up, pals!

195
00:07:09,179 --> 00:07:10,598
This is your night!

196
00:07:10,681 --> 00:07:11,473
Hey, hey!

197
00:07:11,557 --> 00:07:12,766
Careful with the finish.

198
00:07:12,850 --> 00:07:14,476
That buggy's ready to blast.

199
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:17,271
[ gulping ]

200
00:07:17,354 --> 00:07:19,148
Yo! Party animals!

201
00:07:19,231 --> 00:07:20,482
Still hungry?

202
00:07:20,566 --> 00:07:22,151
Mm-nn-mm.

203
00:07:22,234 --> 00:07:24,612
Come on.
Tree Spirit says!

204
00:07:24,695 --> 00:07:26,530
Scoop it till you poop it!

205
00:07:26,614 --> 00:07:30,242
Let's get gross!

206
00:07:30,326 --> 00:07:31,160
BOY:
Finn?

207
00:07:31,243 --> 00:07:32,411
Oh. Sorry.

208
00:07:32,494 --> 00:07:35,497
So...you guys want to
learn another one?

209
00:07:35,581 --> 00:07:37,124
Okay, watch this.

210
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:39,418
[ snapping rhythmically ]

211
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:43,339
[ chuckles ]
Cute.

212
00:07:43,422 --> 00:07:45,049
Uh, hey...

213
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:47,760
So, you guys really
believe in the Tree Spirit?

214
00:07:47,843 --> 00:07:49,345
Eh, not really,
| guess.

215
00:07:49,428 --> 00:07:51,430
We're kind of just
looking to help out.

216
00:07:51,513 --> 00:07:52,389
Hmm.

217
00:07:52,473 --> 00:07:54,642
Hey!
It's Finn with the grin!

218
00:07:54,725 --> 00:07:56,226
Mind if | sit down?

219
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:57,811
[ grunts ]

220
00:07:57,895 --> 00:07:59,438
[ laughs ]
Look at this!

221
00:07:59,521 --> 00:08:01,649
You ever see
someone sit like this?

222
00:08:01,732 --> 00:08:03,442
| guess not.

223
00:08:03,525 --> 00:08:04,318
Hey, Martin?

224
00:08:04,401 --> 00:08:05,527
Yeah?

225
00:08:05,611 --> 00:08:08,530
Uh, I think | really need
some answers to stuff --

226
00:08:08,614 --> 00:08:11,533
like where did | come
from or who's my mom?

227
00:08:11,617 --> 00:08:12,409
[ laughs ]

228
00:08:12,493 --> 00:08:13,327
Whoops.

229
00:08:13,410 --> 00:08:14,787
[ chuckles ]

230
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,497
[ sighs ]

231
00:08:16,580 --> 00:08:18,415
Okay, uh,
long story short --

232
00:08:18,499 --> 00:08:20,084
you were born on a...

233
00:08:20,167 --> 00:08:21,293
boat...I guess.

234
00:08:21,377 --> 00:08:23,337
Like a...banana boat...

235
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:24,338
[ thunder crashes ]

236
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:25,547
...in the middle
of the ocean.

237
00:08:25,631 --> 00:08:28,842
So all kinds of stuff
tried to eat you --

238
00:08:28,926 --> 00:08:31,095
whales and fish...

239
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:33,222
squids.

240
00:08:33,305 --> 00:08:35,641
Uh, there was a tiger...

241
00:08:35,724 --> 00:08:37,101
[ tiger snarls ]

242
00:08:37,184 --> 00:08:38,686
...and...

243
00:08:38,769 --> 00:08:39,728
seaweeds.

244
00:08:39,812 --> 00:08:41,647
The sea's weeds.

245
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:43,023
[ babbles ]

246
00:08:43,107 --> 00:08:44,775
Your mom was...okay.

247
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:45,693
| don't know.

248
00:08:45,776 --> 00:08:47,653
Talking about it
stresses me out.

249
00:08:47,736 --> 00:08:49,154
Maybe later.

250
00:08:49,238 --> 00:08:52,157
So, one day, | got called
on a dangerous mission --

251
00:08:52,241 --> 00:08:55,703
no, like a dangerous
life choice,

252
00:08:55,786 --> 00:08:58,330
two roads diverging in
the night and all that.

253
00:08:58,414 --> 00:09:00,290
And | couldn't
bring you along.

254
00:09:00,374 --> 00:09:03,335
| always planned to come
back for you, but | didn't.

255
00:09:03,419 --> 00:09:06,714
That's...true.

256
00:09:06,797 --> 00:09:08,465
The end!

257
00:09:11,218 --> 00:09:12,136
Look out!

258
00:09:17,766 --> 00:09:20,060
Everything is ruined.

259
00:09:20,144 --> 00:09:22,104
Everyone is fat.

260
00:09:23,647 --> 00:09:26,191
Aah!

261
00:09:26,275 --> 00:09:27,568
[ gasps ]

262
00:09:27,651 --> 00:09:28,861
Martin!

263
00:09:28,944 --> 00:09:30,195
Again?

264
00:09:30,279 --> 00:09:31,780
Oh, good morning,
sweetie!

265
00:09:31,864 --> 00:09:33,407
Martin,
are you leaving?!

266
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:34,867
| absolutely gotta, kid.

267
00:09:34,950 --> 00:09:37,745
| got pressures on me,
stuff you wouldn't understand.

268
00:09:37,828 --> 00:09:40,122
But what about
the villagers?!

269
00:09:40,205 --> 00:09:41,874
That ship looks like
it's gonna blow up!

270
00:09:41,957 --> 00:09:43,709
Uhhhhh...maybe.

271
00:09:43,792 --> 00:09:44,626
| don't know.

272
00:09:44,710 --> 00:09:46,086
Maybe it won't blow up.

273
00:09:46,170 --> 00:09:49,214
I've seen 100 things weirder
than a ship not blowing up.

274
